definition.value: Cardinal organ part which is bounded predominantly by bonafide boundaries.  Examples: lobe of lung, osteon, acinus, submucosa, anterior leaflet of mitral valve, capsule of kidney, cortical bone, muscle fasciculus.
Striated muscle cell which has as its direct parts one or two centrally placed nuclei.
Tissue which consists of cardiac myocytes surrounded by cardiac endomysium.  Examples: Cardiac muscle tissue proper, conducting tissue of heart.
Tissue which consists of skeletal muscle fibers surrounded by endomysium.  Examples: Skeletal muscle tissue of biceps, Skeletal muscle tissue of diaphragm.
Tissue which consists of smooth muscle fibers surrounded by a reticulum of collagen and elastic fibers.  Examples: Arrector muscle of hair, Muscularis mucosae.
Muscle cell which has as its direct parts myofilaments attached to cytoplasmic dense bodies.
Simple squamous epithelium of mesodermal origin which lines serous membranes. Examples: mesothelium of pleura, mesothelium of peritoneum.
